    <h1> my lifestyle</h1>
      <p>
         A lifestyle routine is a set of daily habits and activities that help you stay balanced,
         healthy, and productive. It shapes how you live, <br> feel, and perform each day.
         Having a good routine brings structure, reduces stress, and improves both physical
         and mental well-being.
     </p> 
     <p> Examples of lifestyle routines include:</p>
      <ol>
          <li>
              Morning Routine: Waking up early, stretching, praying or meditating, eating a
                   healthy breakfast, and planning your day.
          </li>
               <li>
                   Self-Care Routine: Taking care of your body, skin, and hair; spending time
                   relaxing; and doing activities that make you happy.
               </li>
               <li>
                   Fitness Routine: Regular exercise like walking, yoga, or gym workouts to stay
                   active and strong.
               </li>
          <li>
              Night Routine: Reflecting on your day, reading, skincare, and sleeping early to
                   recharge.
          </li>
      </ol> <h3>Benefits of maintaining routines:</h3>
      <ol>
          <li>Builds discipline and consistency</li>
          <li>
              Improves mood and focus</li>
          <li> Promotes healthy habits and reduces anxiety  </li>
          <li>  Helps manage time effectively</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
          A good lifestyle routine is personal ‚Äî it should fit your goals, values, and
               personality while keeping you feeling your best every day
      .</p>
